<refentry id="libc-srandom-r-1">

<refmeta>
<refentrytitle>srandom_r</refentrytitle>
<refmiscinfo>libc</refmiscinfo>
</refmeta>

<refnamediv>
<refname>srandom_r</refname>
<refpurpose>reentrantly set the seed for a new sequence of pseudorandom numbers</refpurpose>
<indexterm id="ix-libc-srandom-r-1">
	<primary>srandom_r</primary></indexterm>
</refnamediv>
<refsynopsisdiv>
<funcsynopsis>
<funcsynopsisinfo>
#include &lt;stdlib.h&gt;
</funcsynopsisinfo><funcprototype>
<funcdef>int
<function>srandom_r</function>
</funcdef>
<paramdef>unsigned int
<parameter>seed</parameter>
</paramdef>
<paramdef>struct random_data *
<parameter>buffer</parameter>
</paramdef>

</funcprototype>
</funcsynopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>
<refsect1>
<title>Description</title>
<para>
The interface <function>srandom_r</function> shall function in the same
way as the interface <function>srandom</function>, except that
<function>srandom_r</function> shall
use the data in
<parameter>buffer</parameter> instead of the global random 
number generator state.
</para>
</refsect1>
